Class

exports

exports(ownerId, contractId, options)

Represents a contract in the EVE Online universe. The Contract class allows for the retrieval of contract details, items, and bids related to a specific contract. It can handle contracts associated with a character or corporation depending on the provided scope.

Constructor

# new exports(ownerId, contractId, options)

Creates an instance of the Contract class.

Parameters:
Name Type Description
ownerId number

The unique ID of the contract owner (character or corporation).
contractId number

The unique ID of the contract.
options Object

Configuration options for contract scope and authentication.
auth Object | null

The authentication object required for API requests (null for public contracts).
scope string

The scope of the contract, can be either 'character' or 'corporation'.

# zkb

View Source Killmail.js, line 50

exports(corporationId, authopt)

Represents a corporation in the EVE Online universe. The Corporation class allows for the retrieval and management of corporation-specific data such as divisions, members, shareholder information, standings, starbases, facilities, and much more. This class interacts with the EVE Swagger Interface to fetch and manipulate corporation data.

# zkb

View Source Killmail.js, line 50

exports(characterId, authopt, memberData)

Represents a corporation member in the EVE Online universe. A CorporationMember is a specific type of Character who is a member of a corporation. This class adds additional properties such as start date, location, ship type, and logoff date.

Constructor

# new exports(characterId, authopt, memberData)

Creates an instance of the CorporationMember class. This class extends the Character class to include additional details specific to corporation membership.

Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Default Description
characterId number

The unique ID of the character.
auth Object | null <optional>
 null

The authentication object for the character.
memberData Object

Additional data specific to the corporation member.
startDate string | null

The start date of the member's corporation membership.
locationId number | null

The ID of the current location of the member.
shipTypeId number | null

The ID of the ship the member is currently flying.
logoffDate string | null

The logoff date of the member.

Represents the dogma system in the EVE Online universe. Dogma defines attributes, effects, and items, which influence ships, modules, and other in-game objects. This class allows retrieval and management of dogma attributes and effects, and associates them with items.

exports(effectData)

Represents an effect in the EVE Online universe. Effects are attributes or modifiers applied to various entities in the game, such as ships, modules, or items.

Constructor

# new exports(effectData)

Creates an instance of the Effect class.

Parameters:
Name Type Description
effectData Object

The data for the effect.
effect_id number

The unique ID of the effect.
name string

The name of the effect.
description string

The description of the effect.
icon_id number

The ID of the icon associated with the effect.
is_assistance boolean

Whether the effect provides assistance.
is_offensive boolean

Whether the effect is offensive.
is_warp_safe boolean

Whether the effect is warp-safe.
pre_expression string

The pre-expression formula of the effect, if applicable.
post_expression string

The post-expression formula of the effect, if applicable.

# zkb

View Source Killmail.js, line 50

exports(eventData)

Represents an event in a system, such as a meeting or appointment. The Event class allows for the creation, management, and tracking of event details, including attendees and responses.

Constructor

# new exports(eventData)

Creates an instance of the Event class.

Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Default Description
eventData Object

The data for the event.
event_id number

The unique ID of the event.
event_date string

The date of the event (in ISO 8601 format).
title string

The title of the event.
text string

The description of the event.
importance string

The importance level of the event (e.g., "high", "low").
owner_id number

The ID of the event owner (typically the organizer).
response string | null <optional>
 null

The response from the attendee (e.g., "accepted", "declined"), or null if not yet responded.

# zkb

View Source Killmail.js, line 50

exports(facilityData)

Represents a facility in the EVE Online universe. A facility is an entity, such as a structure or station, controlled by an owner in a specific solar system and region.

Constructor

# new exports(facilityData)

Creates an instance of the Facility class.

Parameters:
Name Type Description
facilityData Object

The data for the facility.
facility_id number

The unique ID of the facility.
owner_id number

The ID of the owner of the facility.
region_id number

The ID of the region where the facility is located.
solar_system_id number

The ID of the solar system where the facility is located.
tax number

The tax rate for using the facility.
type_id number

The type ID of the facility, which corresponds to the type of structure or station.

exports(factionData)

Represents a faction in the EVE Online universe. This class holds information about a faction, including its name, description, associated corporation, and statistics such as the number of stations.

Constructor

# new exports(factionData)

Creates an instance of the Faction class.

Parameters:
Name Type Description
factionData Object

The data for the faction.
faction_id number

The unique ID of the faction.
name string

The name of the faction.
description string

The description of the faction.
solar_system_id number

The ID of the home solar system of the faction.
corporation_id number

The ID of the corporation associated with the faction.
size_factor number

A factor representing the size of the faction.
station_count number

The number of stations controlled by the faction.
station_system_count number

The number of systems containing stations controlled by the faction.
militia_corporation_id number

The ID of the militia corporation associated with the faction.

exports(fittingData)

View Source Killmail.js, line 50

exports(fleetId, auth)

Represents a Fleet in the EVE Online universe. The Fleet class interacts with the EVE Swagger Interface to retrieve and manage fleet information, including fleet details, wings, and members. This class is responsible for ensuring authentication, loading fleet data, and formatting data into JSON.
